result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) and Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs) was dismissed by the court.

  • Dawn M Hackel was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Dawn M Hackel in court with Attorney Ronald James Sonderhouse.  Pablo Galaviz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a plea to Count #1.   Court performs colloquy with Defendant and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1.  Count #2 is dismissed by operation of law.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Sonderhouse makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1: WITHHELD SENTENCE:   

*D/L REVOCATION: 24 months.
*IGNITION INTERLOCK: 24 months.

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEARS;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done 
*Attend Victim Impact Panel on:  3/2/16. Defendant to serve 30 days huber, consecutive, as penalty for failure to attend Victim Impact Panel.
FINE: $1,582.00 & $250.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid out of cash bail posted ($1,000.00) and remainder due as a condition of probation)

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35.00 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forward to Waukesha County Sheriff's Department. 


CONDITION TIME:  6 MONTHS,  Non-working hours with standard release conditions to commence forthwith.  Defendant taken into custody
